 diameter steel plate.<br>
2. The H- bombs are detonated at 3000<br>
meters behind Orion.<br>
3.This is a 2 stage Orion thermonuclear  starship.<br>
 Both stages use the same pulse units, and both<br>
 stages have a mass ratio of 5/1.<br>
4.Its lift off  weight is 2,000,000,000 kilograms .<br>
5.Both  Orion stages Have a 5/1 mass ratio.<br>
6.  This orion starship is in the shape of a pyramid.<br>
7.The thinner upper  part of the pyramid contains the<br>
 habitat section.This orion measures 3000 meters diameter<br>
at the base by 3000 meters long at the top of the pyramid.<br>
8. The 3000 meter pusher plate is backed by very massive<br>
steel pneumonic springs.The springs are 100  by 10 meters <br>
in length. There are 30 of them behind the pusher plate .<br>
9. The pu ejecter has a diameter of 2 meters.<br>
10.The pus are 2 meters wide, and 2 meters long.<br>
11. The pus are 3 stage teller-ulam configuration<br>
FFF type  H-Bombs that have 450 pounds of lithium <br>
6 duteride fuel wrapped in a 100 kilogram U-238 metal<br>
 casing. <br>
12. The pu trigger is a 44-132   kiloton Gun type atomic <br>
fission trigger.The trigger has a 7 inch diameter<br>
50% complete hemisphere shaped target made of 30<br>
 kilograms of 100%  pure U 235.<br>
13. There is a 7 inch  diameter 30 Kilogram hemisphere<br>
 of  U235 metal at one end of it.It is weilded inside of<br>
a 1 inch thick hollow hemisphere of berylium metal<br>
14. The target is backed by a 3 inch thick steel stopper<br>
 wall behind it at the end of the 1 meter long steel gun<br>
 barrel.<br>
15.The other end of the 8 inch  diameter gun barrel<br>
 contains a 7 inch  inch  wide by 3.5 inch long hemisphere<br>
 of  pure U-235 metal with a mass of 15 kilograms.<br>
16.It is also wielded inside of a 1 inch thick hollow<br>
 hemisphere of berylium metal.<br>
17.It is placed inside of an 8 inch diameter cartridge of<br>
steel that contains 1.5 kilograms of cordite gunpowder<br>
behind it.This steel cartridge is wielded to the gun barrel.<br>
There is a radio remote controled detonator attached to the center of the back end of this cartridge.<br>
18. A 100 kilogram U- 238 cylinder that contains 450 kilograms of lithium 6 dueteride is weilded behind the<br>
 target stopper wall, which is wielded behind the<br>
U 235 pit.<br>
19. The whole assembly(physics package) is then placed inside of a  cylidrical passage inside of 2 meter by 2 meter hollow cylinder made of lead metal.   <br>
 <br>
20. A radio signal is used to detonate the pu at 3000 meters behind the pusher plate.The pu ejector throws the pu out at<br>
10 meters a second . It is detonated exactly 300 seconds after pu ejection occurrs. The pu generates a 9-10<br>
megaton Thermonuclear explosion when it is triggered..<br>
 <br>
21. The pus have a debris velocity of 27,000 kilometers/sec.<br>
about .09 C which is ( 9% of light velocity)<br>
22. Each pu has a mass of 5000 kilograms.<br>
23.A 50% cllimation of the debris is achieved by the impulse<br>
absorber.<br>
24. The thermonuclear fireball created by the pu detonation<br>
will achieve a maximium diameter of 3000 meters, at max expansion which matches the diameter of the pusher plate.<br>
25. This means that 2500 kg * 27,000,000 meter/sec <br>
will be the momentum transferred to the pusher plate by<br>
 each pu detonation.<br>
26. This is 6.75 * 10 to the 10th power kilograms of momentum force.This Orion has a mass of 2,000,000,000<br>
kilograms. Each pu will boost Orion by 33.5 gs which is<br>
335 meters a second. The Pneomonic springs will absorb<br>
and store  this impact force, and reduce the  Acceleration by their expansion to 1 G per second for each detonation or less.<br>
27.On earth in the atmosphere the pu detonation would result in a 200 - 700 mile per hour wind containing at least 2,000,000,000 kilograms of air sweeping out from the thermonuclear fireball for a blast radius of 20 something miles from ground  zero that could easily demolish even the worlds largest cities by blast alone. Orion can withstand this force because of its steel armoured pusher plate et el:  but a city on earth could not do this.Let such bombs be used peacefully to power Orions,  but let them never used for nuclear war on Earth we hope.*In a nuclear war on earth this 10 megaton blast created by the Orion pus  could easily result in somewhere between 10,000,000, and 20,000,000 fatalities in just a few minutes , and at least a 40 something mile diameter circle of complete Thermonuclear  distruction.<br>
28. With a 50% collimation and a debris velocity of <br>
27,000,000 meter/sec One Orion stage with a mass ratio of<br>
5/1 using these pulse units can accelerate to about 8% of light velocity in just a few months,while carrying a useful payload of millions of tons.That is about 14,000 miles per second or 50,000,000 miles per hour. An H2 + O2   chemical rocket with Si = 450 seconds , and with 3 5/1 mass ratio <br>
stages stacked on top of each other , can do just about<br>
 50,000 miles per hour when compared to Orion.<br>
29.Orion is a non relatavistic starship but it is very well<br>
suited for a human Crewed Battlestar Galactica style <br>
interstellar expedition to find, and colonize a new earth, in another star system such as maybe Epsilon Eridani  for the human  race, Because of the time factor  Orion must be either<br>
a sleeper ship (crew in suspended animation ) Or a multigenerational vessel however.It takes 50 years to reach<br>
the nearest stars at 8% of light speed, and 130 years to reach Epsilon Eridani at 11 light years distance with this orion.<br>
30.Orion would also take about 110 years to reach Sirius for example, and 208 years to Reach the star Vega at 16 light years from Sol.Vega is the brightest star in the sky, and has<br>
a brilliant blue color.<br>
31.How many people would volunteer to ride Orion to a star<br>
on such a mission?<br>
32.Should Orion cruise at .08 C and save stage two for<br>
 deceleration?, OR Should Orion use both stages to reach<br>
.16 C, never declerate, and become an interstellar cycler?<br>
33. If you go the interstellar cycler route perhaps Orion could<br>
cruise around the Galaxy forever in Galactic orbit at .16 C<br>
and use small Deadalas class fusion microexplosion drive <br>
Starships  based in its hangars  to send people to the stars that Orion will pass on its literaly everlasting  orbit around the Milky Way Galaxy at .16 C. Other small fusion drive starships,<br>
or even M.A.M.A  drive starships built centuries after orion    was launched could dock with Orion, and ride Orion around the galaxy literally forever, and then leave it  when ever <br>
Orion passes a star they want to visit in its galactic orbit.<br>
34 . Any question comments or discussian about these <br>
things?<br>
. <br>
