 Even Orion is a piss-poor interstellar ship.<br>
 Probes like StarWisp lead the way, nomadic cometary colonists eventually find their way, while the solar system is built up.<br>
 If it takes a few generations or centuries to get there, you might as well consider them as space people, so why would they look for other cold, dark gravity holes to go down to? When it comes to that, why bother to build a hugely expensive ship to coop yourself up in, when there are all these tasty comets out there, and all you need is a mirror factory?<br>
 Colonise asteroids and comets, living in space colonies. Use Orion to get there quickly &amp; safely.<br>
 Worry about interstellar when we're running out of room to build in the ecliptic in the Dyson Cloud we'll build around the Sun (a few millennia, probably). Maybe then use laser sails to push magsail decelerated crewed ships to colonise the Oort clouds and asteroids of neighboring stars. Build up to Savage's interstellar EM catapult, for rapid &amp; routine interstellar travel (for .999C, you spend a few months at either end of the trip in aceleration couches, and a couple of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>days</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> between stars...)<br>
