<br>
 This orion like its fusion version can drive a useful<br>
payload of millions of tons to the 9 planets, and into <br>
the kuiper Belt. At .01 C it takes 100 years to go one light year. <br>
<br>
 Maximium round trip delta v for the two stage fission orion would be about .0025 C., which is <br>
750 km/sec. For this reason the kuiper belt is the <br>
most distant practical  destination for this orion.<br>
At .0025 C you can travel 15,000,000,000 miles in one<br>
year. All though they acclerate much more slowly<br>
these velocities can also be achieved by high power nuclear electric ion, and plasma drive rockets.<br>
<br>
Deadalas is twice as fast as fusion orions, and twice as<br>
efficent. Nep can go eqauly  as fast or even faster then fission type orions, all though it might accelerate at only<br>
say .001 G.<br>
<br>
For these reasons,  Orion class nuclear bomb rockets are<br>
in fact antiquated, backward, and obselete, unless there<br>
is a need to move a payload of miillions of tons around.<br>
